com.badlogic.gdx.ai.pfa

Interface HierarchicalGraph<N>

  • Type Parameters:
    N - Type of node
    All Superinterfaces:
    Graph<N>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    IndexedHierarchicalGraph

    public interface HierarchicalGraph<N>
extends Graph<N>
    A HierarchicalGraph is a multilevel graph that can be traversed by a HierarchicalPathFinder at any level of its hierarchy.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      N convertNodeBetweenLevels(int inputLevel, N node, int outputLevel)
      Converts the node at the input level into a node at the output level.
      int getLevelCount()
      Returns the number of levels in this hierarchical graph.
      void setLevel(int level)
      Switches the graph into the given level so all future calls to the getConnections methods act as if the graph was just a simple, non-hierarchical graph at that level.
